    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="47" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-07-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27,
                            1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Egan reports the acceptance by the Chilean Government of an arbitration
                        to be held in Washington. It proposes that one arbitrator be named by the
                        President of each country, and that the Chief Justice of the Supreme Court
                        of the United States will decide all differences between the two
                        arbitrators. Mr. Egan thinks that if the proposition is not satisfactory,
                        the Chilean Government will agree to have the President of one of the
                        Republics in Europe designate a third arbitrator.</p>
            </div>
